According to classes.berkeley.edu:
45 reserved for Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences Majors and Undeclared Students in the College of Engineering
122 reserved for College of Letters & Sciences: Freshman Students
1 reserved for New Letters & Sciences Transfer Students
56 reserved for Computer Science Majors in the College of Letters & Science: Sophomore Students
15 reserved for Engineering Science Majors with 3-4 Terms in Attendance
45 reserved for Students with Enrollment Permission

Note that there are no seats reserved for L&S juniors, so that's probably why.

Considering there are still 280 open seats and the class tends to accommodate everyone anyway, you are pretty much sure to get in.
Phew, that's reassuring. When will I get into the class then? Is it on 8/19 when adjustment begins?

As a junior in the same situation, how likely am I to get into EE 16A if I am currently 112 on the waitlist? Does the class tend to expand / do enough people drop such that I could get into the class?

Thanks!

The only issue with getting in after adjustment for EE16A and EE16B will be that you'll most likely be left with really bad times for labs.  Say hello to Friday 5-8pm or something like that.  Unless you get really lucky and have some new labs open up.
